AB  - This study investigates the effects of gate length (Lg) and doping concentration (Nd) on the performance parameters of Arsenene (As) and Antimonene (Sb) monolayer (ML) based sub-5 nm double-gate (DG) junctionless field-effect transistors (JLFETs). Here, quantum transport simulation methods have been used. Key performance parameters such as On-current (Ion) and Sub-threshold Slope (SS) are analyzed from the Id-Vg characteristics of the simulated As/Sb JLFETs. The findings reveal that Ion and SS are linear functions of Lg but increase with Nd, meeting the ITRS requirements for 2028. The simulation results suggest that As/Sb JLFETs with specific Lg and Nd demonstrate superior Ion and SS compared to DG ML As/Sb MOSFETs, making them promising candidates for both high-performance (HP) and low-power (LP) applications. Therefore, ML As and Sb-based JLFETs are confirmed to be promising nano-devices for future applications.
