AB  - This research work presents an overview of BuildSysPro-QAI, a new Modelica library used to assess the thermo-hygro-aerodynamic behaviour and transport of pollutants, as well as the interaction of pollutants with walls, inside residential and tertiary buildings. A demonstration of a multi-zone and multi-physics 0D-1D simulation including indoor air quality IAQ, humidity, aeraulic and thermal exchanges is performed. The use-case evaluates an efficient French residential house (RE 2020) with heat pump for heating system and a self-regulating ventilation system.
