AB  - The simulation of quantum transport in semiconductor devices is time-consuming, and methods to reduce computation cost are required. In this paper, we propose a method to accelerate the quantum transport simulation of FinFET by using convolutional neural network (CNN) to get a relatively accurate initial guess of potential distribution, which can effectively reduce the number of iteration loops. Geometrical parameters, doping concentration and applied voltage are set as the input of CNN model, the potential distribution in cross section of FinFET with different geometrical parameters, doping concentrations and applied voltage can be obtained. Compared with the traditional method which sets the initial potential distribution to be a specific value according to applied voltage, our proposed method can reduce the simulation time by 45%.
