AB  - The proceedings contain 19 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Bildverarbeitung - Image Processing. The topics include: The future of machine vision: AI software designed with users in mind; constrained hand-multiple-eyes calibration; machine learning-based battery electrode foil inspection; deep learning-based localisation of combine harvester components in thermal images; noise analysis of a synthetically rendered scene in sensor-realistic image simulation; performance comparison of area-scan and event-based camera; benefiting from quantum? A comparative study of Q-Seg, quantum-inspired techniques, and U-Net for crack segmentation; Fast semantic segmentation CNNs for FPGAs; semantic segmentation and uncertainty quantification with vision transformers for industrial applications; evaluation of multi-task uncertainties in joint semantic segmentation and monocular depth estimation; Evaluation of 3D-LiDAR based person detection algorithms for edge computing; explainable fatigue detection in assembly tasks through graph neural networks; visual car brand classification by implementing a synthetic image dataset creation pipeline; robust traffic light detection and stopline release by map association for automated driving; AI scratching your car: Using diffusion models for training data generation in automotive damage detection; image stitching using gradual image warping in autonomous driving; image stitching using gradual image warping in autonomous driving.
