AB  - The proceedings contain 31 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Service-Oriented Computing. The topics include: Towards Improving Insurance Processes: A Time Series Analysis of Psychosocial Recovery After Workplace Injury Across Legislative Environments; Uncovering LLMs for Service-Composition: Challenges and Opportunities; transformative Predictive Modelling in the Business of Health: Harnessing Decision Trees for Strategic Insights and Enhanced Operational Efficiency; breaking Boundaries: Can a Unified Hardware Abstraction Layer Simplify Transformer Deployments on Edge Devices?; Improving Deep Learning Transparency: Leveraging the Power of LIME Heatmap; non-expert Level Analysis of Self-adaptive Systems; federated Data Products: A Confluence of Data Mesh and Gaia-X for Data Sharing; XPS++: A Publish/Subscribe System with Built-In Security and Privacy by Design; on Rounding Errors in the Simulation of Quantum Circuits; linear Structure of Training Samples in Quantum Neural Network Applications; towards Higher Abstraction Levels in Quantum Computing; hybrid Data Management Architecture for Present Quantum Computing; quantum Block-Matching Algorithm Using Dissimilarity Measure; some Initial Guidelines for Building Reusable Quantum Oracles; Carbon-Awareness in CI/CD; smart Public Transport with Be-in/Be-out System Supported by iBeacon Devices; towards a Systematic Comparison Framework for Cloud Services Customer Agreements; formalizing Microservices Patterns with Event-B: The Case of Service Registry; privacy Engineering in the Data Mesh: Towards a Decentralized Data Privacy Governance Framework; towards a Taxonomy and Software Architecture for Data Processing and Contextualization for the Internet of Things; advanced Serverless Edge Computing; immersive 3D Simulator for Drone-as-a-Service; SLA-Wizard - Automated Configuration of RESTful API Gateways Based on SLAs; The IDL Tool Suite: Inter-parameter Dependency Management in Web APIs; smelling Homemade Crypto Code in Microservices, with KubeHound; what is Blockchain and How Can it Help My Business? (Extended Tutorial Summary); quantum Services: A Tutorial on the Technology and the Process; satellite Computing: From Space to Your Screen.
