AB  - The proceedings contain 27 papers. The topics discussed include: full-band modelling of phonons in polytype Ge and Si; inter-layer coupling effects on vertical electron transport in multilayer graphene nanoribbons; terahertz time-domain spectroscopy characterization of carbon nanostructures embedded in polymer; experimental and theoretical studies of sub-THz detection using strained-Si FETs; transport scaling limits of ovonic devices: a simulative approach; excitation polarization dependence of optical coupled exciton states in a single coupled quantum dot molecule; lateral interdot coupling among dense ensemble of InAs quantum dots grown on InP substrate observed at cryogenic temperatures; dynamic Rabi oscillations in a quantum dot embedded in a nanobridge in the presence of surface acoustic waves; low-temperature performance of semiconducting asymmetric nanochannel diodes; ultrafast control of electron dynamics in 3D topological insulator; efficient Monte Carlo-based algorithms for the wigner transport equation; Monte Carlo simulation of THz radiation detection in GaN MOSFET n+nn+ channel with uncentered gate in n-region; magnetic-optical transitions induced by twisted light in quantum dots; hydrodynamic modelling of terahertz rectification in AlGaN/GaN high electron mobility transistors; optoelectronic and photoacoustic studies of an organic dye synthesized through green route; screening effects of photogenerated carriers on terahertz radiation from coherent GaAs-like longitudinal optical phonons in (11n)-oriented GaAs/In0.1Al0.9As strained multiple quantum wells; thermoelectric current in tubular nanowires in transverse electric and magnetic fields; the issue of 0D-like ground state isolation in GaAs and InP-based coupled quantum dots-quantum well systems; and drift and diffusion high-field magneto-transport in GaN.
